{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"What do I know"},{"time":2000,"text":"that would cause me,"},{"time":4000,"text":"a reticent, Midwestern scientist,"},{"time":6000,"text":"to get myself arrested"},{"time":9000,"text":"in front of the White House protesting?"},{"time":12000,"text":"And what would you do"},{"time":14000,"text":"if you knew what I know?"},{"time":16000,"text":"Let's start with how I got to this point."},{"time":20000,"text":"I was lucky to grow up"},{"time":22000,"text":"at a time when it was not difficult"},{"time":25000,"text":"for the child of a tenant farmer"},{"time":27000,"text":"to make his way to the state university."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29000,"text":"And I was really lucky"},{"time":32000,"text":"to go to the University of Iowa"},{"time":34000,"text":"where I could study under Professor James Van Allen"},{"time":37000,"text":"who built instruments"},{"time":39000,"text":"for the first U.S. satellites."},{"time":41000,"text":"Professor Van Allen told me"},{"time":44000,"text":"about observations of Venus,"},{"time":47000,"text":"that there was intense microwave radiation."},{"time":49000,"text":"Did it mean that Venus had an ionosphere?"},{"time":52000,"text":"Or was Venus extremely hot?"},{"time":54000,"text":"The right answer,"},{"time":56000,"text":"confirmed by the Soviet Venera spacecraft,"},{"time":61000,"text":"was that Venus was very hot --"},{"time":64000,"text":"900 degrees Fahrenheit."},{"time":66000,"text":"And it was kept hot"},{"time":68000,"text":"by a thick carbon dioxide atmosphere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71000,"text":"I was fortunate to join NASA"},{"time":73000,"text":"and successfully propose"},{"time":75000,"text":"an experiment to fly to Venus."},{"time":77000,"text":"Our instrument took this image"},{"time":80000,"text":"of the veil of Venus,"},{"time":82000,"text":"which turned out to be"},{"time":84000,"text":"a smog of sulfuric acid."},{"time":87000,"text":"But while our instrument was being built,"},{"time":90000,"text":"I became involved in calculations"},{"time":92000,"text":"of the greenhouse effect"},{"time":94000,"text":"here on Earth,"},{"time":96000,"text":"because we realized"},{"time":98000,"text":"that our atmospheric composition was changing."},{"time":101000,"text":"Eventually, I resigned"},{"time":103000,"text":"as principal investigator"},{"time":105000,"text":"on our Venus experiment"},{"time":107000,"text":"because a planet changing before our eyes"},{"time":110000,"text":"is more interesting and important."},{"time":112000,"text":"Its changes will affect all of humanity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115000,"text":"The greenhouse effect had been well understood"},{"time":117000,"text":"for more than a century."},{"time":119000,"text":"British physicist John Tyndall,"},{"time":121000,"text":"in the 1850's,"},{"time":123000,"text":"made laboratory measurements"},{"time":125000,"text":"of the infrared radiation,"},{"time":127000,"text":"which is heat."},{"time":129000,"text":"And he showed that gasses such as CO2 absorb heat,"},{"time":132000,"text":"thus acting like a blanket"},{"time":135000,"text":"warming Earth's surface."}]},{"cues":[{"time":137000,"text":"I worked with other scientists"},{"time":139000,"text":"to analyze Earth climate observations."},{"time":143000,"text":"In 1981,"},{"time":145000,"text":"we published an article in Science magazine"},{"time":148000,"text":"concluding that observed warming"},{"time":150000,"text":"of 0.4 degrees Celsius"},{"time":152000,"text":"in the prior century"},{"time":154000,"text":"was consistent with the greenhouse effect"},{"time":156000,"text":"of increasing CO2."},{"time":158000,"text":"That Earth would likely warm in the 1980's,"},{"time":161000,"text":"and warming would exceed"},{"time":163000,"text":"the noise level of random weather"},{"time":165000,"text":"by the end of the century."},{"time":167000,"text":"We also said that the 21st century"},{"time":170000,"text":"would see shifting climate zones,"},{"time":172000,"text":"creation of drought-prone regions"},{"time":174000,"text":"in North America and Asia,"},{"time":176000,"text":"erosion of ice sheets, rising sea levels"},{"time":179000,"text":"and opening of the fabled Northwest Passage."},{"time":182000,"text":"All of these impacts"},{"time":184000,"text":"have since either happened"},{"time":186000,"text":"or are now well under way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":188000,"text":"That paper was reported on the front page of the New York Times"},{"time":192000,"text":"and led to me testifying to Congress"},{"time":194000,"text":"in the 1980's,"},{"time":196000,"text":"testimony in which I emphasized"},{"time":199000,"text":"that global warming increases both extremes"},{"time":202000,"text":"of the Earth's water cycle."},{"time":205000,"text":"Heatwaves and droughts on one hand,"},{"time":207000,"text":"directly from the warming,"},{"time":209000,"text":"but also, because a warmer atmosphere"},{"time":211000,"text":"holds more water vapor"},{"time":213000,"text":"with its latent energy,"},{"time":215000,"text":"rainfall will become"},{"time":217000,"text":"in more extreme events."},{"time":219000,"text":"There will be stronger storms and greater flooding."},{"time":222000,"text":"Global warming hoopla"},{"time":225000,"text":"became time-consuming"},{"time":227000,"text":"and distracted me from doing science --"},{"time":229000,"text":"partly because I had complained"},{"time":231000,"text":"that the White House altered my testimony."},{"time":234000,"text":"So I decided to go back"},{"time":236000,"text":"to strictly doing science"},{"time":238000,"text":"and leave the communication to others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242000,"text":"By 15 years later,"},{"time":245000,"text":"evidence of global warming was much stronger."},{"time":248000,"text":"Most of the things mentioned in our 1981 paper"},{"time":251000,"text":"were facts."},{"time":253000,"text":"I had the privilege to speak twice"},{"time":256000,"text":"to the president's climate task force."},{"time":258000,"text":"But energy policies continued to focus"},{"time":261000,"text":"on finding more fossil fuels."},{"time":264000,"text":"By then we had two grandchildren,"},{"time":267000,"text":"Sophie and Connor."},{"time":269000,"text":"I decided"},{"time":271000,"text":"that I did not want them in the future"},{"time":273000,"text":"to say, \"Opa understood what was happening,"},{"time":275000,"text":"but he didn't make it clear.\""},{"time":277000,"text":"So I decided to give a public talk"},{"time":280000,"text":"criticizing the lack of an appropriate energy policy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283000,"text":"I gave the talk at the University of Iowa in 2004"},{"time":286000,"text":"and at the 2005 meeting"},{"time":289000,"text":"of the American Geophysical Union."},{"time":292000,"text":"This led to calls"},{"time":294000,"text":"from the White House to NASA headquarters"},{"time":296000,"text":"and I was told that I could not give any talks or speak with the media"},{"time":299000,"text":"without prior explicit approval"},{"time":302000,"text":"by NASA headquarters."},{"time":305000,"text":"After I informed the New York Times"},{"time":307000,"text":"about these restrictions,"},{"time":309000,"text":"NASA was forced to end the censorship."},{"time":312000,"text":"But there were consequences."},{"time":314000,"text":"I had been using the first line"},{"time":316000,"text":"of the NASA mission statement,"},{"time":318000,"text":"\"To understand and protect the home planet,\""},{"time":321000,"text":"to justify my talks."},{"time":323000,"text":"Soon the first line of the mission statement"},{"time":325000,"text":"was deleted, never to appear again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":329000,"text":"Over the next few years"},{"time":331000,"text":"I was drawn more and more"},{"time":333000,"text":"into trying to communicate the urgency"},{"time":336000,"text":"of a change in energy policies,"},{"time":339000,"text":"while still researching the physics of climate change."},{"time":342000,"text":"Let me describe the most important conclusion from the physics --"},{"time":345000,"text":"first, from Earth's energy balance"},{"time":348000,"text":"and, second, from Earth's climate history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352000,"text":"Adding CO2 to the air"},{"time":354000,"text":"is like throwing another blanket on the bed."},{"time":357000,"text":"It reduces Earth's heat radiation to space,"},{"time":360000,"text":"so there's a temporary energy imbalance."},{"time":363000,"text":"More energy is coming in"},{"time":365000,"text":"than going out,"},{"time":367000,"text":"until Earth warms up enough"},{"time":369000,"text":"to again radiate to space"},{"time":371000,"text":"as much energy as it absorbs from the Sun."},{"time":373000,"text":"So the key quantity"},{"time":375000,"text":"is Earth's energy imbalance."},{"time":378000,"text":"Is there more energy coming in"},{"time":380000,"text":"than going out?"},{"time":382000,"text":"If so, more warming is in the pipeline."},{"time":385000,"text":"It will occur without adding any more greenhouse gasses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389000,"text":"Now finally,"},{"time":391000,"text":"we can measure Earth's energy imbalance precisely"},{"time":395000,"text":"by measuring the heat content"},{"time":397000,"text":"in Earth's heat reservoirs."},{"time":400000,"text":"The biggest reservoir, the ocean, was the least well measured,"},{"time":403000,"text":"until more than 3,000 Argo floats"},{"time":406000,"text":"were distributed around the world's ocean."},{"time":409000,"text":"These floats reveal"},{"time":411000,"text":"that the upper half of the ocean"},{"time":413000,"text":"is gaining heat at a substantial rate."},{"time":416000,"text":"The deep ocean is also gaining heat at a smaller rate,"},{"time":419000,"text":"and energy is going"},{"time":421000,"text":"into the net melting of ice all around the planet."},{"time":424000,"text":"And the land, to depths of tens of meters,"},{"time":427000,"text":"is also warming."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429000,"text":"The total energy imbalance now"},{"time":432000,"text":"is about six-tenths of a watt per square meter."},{"time":436000,"text":"That may not sound like much,"},{"time":438000,"text":"but when added up over the whole world, it's enormous."},{"time":441000,"text":"It's about 20 times greater"},{"time":444000,"text":"than the rate of energy use by all of humanity."},{"time":447000,"text":"It's equivalent to exploding"},{"time":449000,"text":"400,000 Hiroshima atomic bombs per day"},{"time":455000,"text":"365 days per year."},{"time":458000,"text":"That's how much extra energy"},{"time":460000,"text":"Earth is gaining each day."},{"time":462000,"text":"This imbalance,"},{"time":464000,"text":"if we want to stabilize climate,"},{"time":467000,"text":"means that we must reduce CO2"},{"time":469000,"text":"from 391 ppm, parts per million,"},{"time":472000,"text":"back to 350 ppm."},{"time":475000,"text":"That is the change needed to restore energy balance"},{"time":478000,"text":"and prevent further warming."}]},{"cues":[{"time":480000,"text":"Climate change deniers argue"},{"time":483000,"text":"that the Sun is the main cause of climate change."},{"time":486000,"text":"But the measured energy imbalance occurred"},{"time":489000,"text":"during the deepest solar minimum in the record,"},{"time":493000,"text":"when the Sun's energy reaching Earth was least."},{"time":497000,"text":"Yet, there was more energy coming in than going out."},{"time":500000,"text":"This shows that the effect of the Sun's variations on climate"},{"time":503000,"text":"is overwhelmed by the increasing greenhouse gasses,"},{"time":506000,"text":"mainly from burning fossil fuels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":509000,"text":"Now consider Earth's climate history."},{"time":512000,"text":"These curves for global temperature,"},{"time":514000,"text":"atmospheric CO2 and sea level"},{"time":517000,"text":"were derived from ocean cores and Antarctic ice cores,"},{"time":520000,"text":"from ocean sediments and snowflakes"},{"time":522000,"text":"that piled up year after year"},{"time":525000,"text":"over 800,000 years"},{"time":527000,"text":"forming a two-mile thick ice sheet."},{"time":529000,"text":"As you see, there's a high correlation"},{"time":532000,"text":"between temperature, CO2 and sea level."},{"time":535000,"text":"Careful examination shows"},{"time":537000,"text":"that the temperature changes"},{"time":539000,"text":"slightly lead the CO2 changes"},{"time":541000,"text":"by a few centuries."},{"time":544000,"text":"Climate change deniers like to use this fact"},{"time":547000,"text":"to confuse and trick the public"},{"time":550000,"text":"by saying, \"Look, the temperature causes CO2 to change,"},{"time":553000,"text":"not vice versa.\""},{"time":555000,"text":"But that lag"},{"time":557000,"text":"is exactly what is expected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":560000,"text":"Small changes in Earth's orbit"},{"time":563000,"text":"that occur over tens to hundreds of thousands of years"},{"time":566000,"text":"alter the distribution"},{"time":568000,"text":"of sunlight on Earth."},{"time":570000,"text":"When there is more sunlight"},{"time":572000,"text":"at high latitudes in summer, ice sheets melt."},{"time":575000,"text":"Shrinking ice sheets"},{"time":577000,"text":"make the planet darker,"},{"time":579000,"text":"so it absorbs more sunlight"},{"time":581000,"text":"and becomes warmer."},{"time":583000,"text":"A warmer ocean releases CO2,"},{"time":585000,"text":"just as a warm Coca-Cola does."},{"time":588000,"text":"And more CO2 causes more warming."},{"time":591000,"text":"So CO2, methane, and ice sheets"},{"time":594000,"text":"were feedbacks"},{"time":596000,"text":"that amplified global temperature change"},{"time":599000,"text":"causing these ancient climate oscillations to be huge,"},{"time":602000,"text":"even though the climate change was initiated"},{"time":605000,"text":"by a very weak forcing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":607000,"text":"The important point"},{"time":609000,"text":"is that these same amplifying feedbacks"},{"time":611000,"text":"will occur today."},{"time":613000,"text":"The physics does not change."},{"time":615000,"text":"As Earth warms,"},{"time":617000,"text":"now because of extra CO2 we put in the atmosphere,"},{"time":620000,"text":"ice will melt,"},{"time":622000,"text":"and CO2 and methane will be released"},{"time":624000,"text":"by warming ocean and melting permafrost."},{"time":627000,"text":"While we can't say exactly how fast"},{"time":630000,"text":"these amplifying feedbacks will occur,"},{"time":633000,"text":"it is certain they will occur,"},{"time":636000,"text":"unless we stop the warming."},{"time":638000,"text":"There is evidence"},{"time":640000,"text":"that feedbacks are already beginning."},{"time":643000,"text":"Precise measurements"},{"time":645000,"text":"by GRACE, the gravity satellite,"},{"time":647000,"text":"reveal that both Greenland and Antarctica"},{"time":650000,"text":"are now losing mass,"},{"time":652000,"text":"several hundred cubic kilometers per year."},{"time":655000,"text":"And the rate has accelerated"},{"time":657000,"text":"since the measurements began"},{"time":659000,"text":"nine years ago."},{"time":661000,"text":"Methane is also beginning"},{"time":663000,"text":"to escape from the permafrost."}]},{"cues":[{"time":666000,"text":"What sea level rise"},{"time":668000,"text":"can we look forward to?"},{"time":670000,"text":"The last time CO2 was 390 ppm,"},{"time":673000,"text":"today's value,"},{"time":675000,"text":"sea level was higher"},{"time":677000,"text":"by at least 15 meters, 50 feet."},{"time":680000,"text":"Where you are sitting now"},{"time":682000,"text":"would be under water."},{"time":684000,"text":"Most estimates are that, this century,"},{"time":687000,"text":"we will get at least one meter."},{"time":689000,"text":"I think it will be more"},{"time":691000,"text":"if we keep burning fossil fuels,"},{"time":693000,"text":"perhaps even five meters, which is 18 feet,"},{"time":696000,"text":"this century or shortly thereafter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699000,"text":"The important point"},{"time":701000,"text":"is that we will have started a process"},{"time":704000,"text":"that is out of humanity's control."},{"time":707000,"text":"Ice sheets would continue to disintegrate for centuries."},{"time":710000,"text":"There would be no stable shoreline."},{"time":712000,"text":"The economic consequences are almost unthinkable."},{"time":715000,"text":"Hundreds of New Orleans-like devastations"},{"time":719000,"text":"around the world."},{"time":721000,"text":"What may be more reprehensible,"},{"time":723000,"text":"if climate denial continues,"},{"time":725000,"text":"is extermination of species."},{"time":727000,"text":"The monarch butterfly"},{"time":729000,"text":"could be one of the 20 to 50 percent of all species"},{"time":734000,"text":"that the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change estimates"},{"time":737000,"text":"will be ticketed for extinction"},{"time":739000,"text":"by the end of the century"},{"time":741000,"text":"if we stay on business-as-usual fossil fuel use."}]},{"cues":[{"time":745000,"text":"Global warming is already affecting people."},{"time":748000,"text":"The Texas, Oklahoma, Mexico"},{"time":750000,"text":"heatwave and drought last year,"},{"time":753000,"text":"Moscow the year before"},{"time":755000,"text":"and Europe in 2003,"},{"time":757000,"text":"were all exceptional events,"},{"time":760000,"text":"more than three standard deviations outside the norm."},{"time":764000,"text":"Fifty years ago,"},{"time":766000,"text":"such anomalies"},{"time":768000,"text":"covered only two- to three-tenths"},{"time":770000,"text":"of one percent of the land area."},{"time":772000,"text":"In recent years,"},{"time":774000,"text":"because of global warming,"},{"time":776000,"text":"they now cover about 10 percent --"},{"time":778000,"text":"an increase by a factor of 25 to 50."},{"time":781000,"text":"So we can say with a high degree of confidence"},{"time":784000,"text":"that the severe Texas and Moscow heatwaves"},{"time":786000,"text":"were not natural;"},{"time":788000,"text":"they were caused by global warming."},{"time":791000,"text":"An important impact,"},{"time":793000,"text":"if global warming continues,"},{"time":795000,"text":"will be on the breadbasket of our nation and the world,"},{"time":798000,"text":"the Midwest and Great Plains,"},{"time":800000,"text":"which are expected to become prone to extreme droughts,"},{"time":803000,"text":"worse than the Dust Bowl,"},{"time":805000,"text":"within just a few decades,"},{"time":807000,"text":"if we let global warming continue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":811000,"text":"How did I get dragged deeper and deeper"},{"time":814000,"text":"into an attempt to communicate,"},{"time":816000,"text":"giving talks in 10 countries, getting arrested,"},{"time":819000,"text":"burning up the vacation time"},{"time":821000,"text":"that I had accumulated over 30 years?"},{"time":825000,"text":"More grandchildren helped me along."},{"time":828000,"text":"Jake is a super-positive,"},{"time":830000,"text":"enthusiastic boy."},{"time":833000,"text":"Here at age two and a half years,"},{"time":835000,"text":"he thinks he can protect"},{"time":837000,"text":"his two and a half-day-old little sister."},{"time":840000,"text":"It would be immoral"},{"time":842000,"text":"to leave these young people"},{"time":844000,"text":"with a climate system"},{"time":846000,"text":"spiraling out of control."}]},{"cues":[{"time":848000,"text":"Now the tragedy about climate change"},{"time":851000,"text":"is that we can solve it"},{"time":853000,"text":"with a simple, honest approach"},{"time":855000,"text":"of a gradually rising carbon fee"},{"time":858000,"text":"collected from fossil fuel companies"},{"time":860000,"text":"and distributed 100 percent electronically"},{"time":864000,"text":"every month to all legal residents"},{"time":866000,"text":"on a per capita basis,"},{"time":868000,"text":"with the government not keeping one dime."},{"time":872000,"text":"Most people would get more in the monthly dividend"},{"time":875000,"text":"than they'd pay in increased prices."},{"time":877000,"text":"This fee and dividend"},{"time":879000,"text":"would stimulate the economy"},{"time":881000,"text":"and innovations,"},{"time":883000,"text":"creating millions of jobs."},{"time":885000,"text":"It is the principal requirement"},{"time":887000,"text":"for moving us rapidly"},{"time":890000,"text":"to a clean energy future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":892000,"text":"Several top economists"},{"time":894000,"text":"are coauthors on this proposition."},{"time":897000,"text":"Jim DiPeso of Republicans for Environmental Protection"},{"time":900000,"text":"describes it thusly:"},{"time":902000,"text":"\"Transparent. Market-based."},{"time":904000,"text":"Does not enlarge government."},{"time":906000,"text":"Leaves energy decisions to individual choices."},{"time":909000,"text":"Sounds like a conservative climate plan.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":913000,"text":"But instead of placing a rising fee on carbon emissions"},{"time":917000,"text":"to make fossil fuels pay"},{"time":920000,"text":"their true cost to society,"},{"time":922000,"text":"our governments are forcing the public"},{"time":925000,"text":"to subsidize fossil fuels"},{"time":928000,"text":"by 400 to 500 billion dollars"},{"time":931000,"text":"per year worldwide,"},{"time":933000,"text":"thus encouraging extraction of every fossil fuel --"},{"time":936000,"text":"mountaintop removal,"},{"time":938000,"text":"longwall mining, fracking,"},{"time":940000,"text":"tar sands, tar shale,"},{"time":942000,"text":"deep ocean Arctic drilling."},{"time":945000,"text":"This path, if continued,"},{"time":947000,"text":"guarantees that we will pass tipping points"},{"time":950000,"text":"leading to ice sheet disintegration"},{"time":952000,"text":"that will accelerate out of control of future generations."},{"time":956000,"text":"A large fraction of species"},{"time":958000,"text":"will be committed to extinction."},{"time":960000,"text":"And increasing intensity of droughts and floods"},{"time":962000,"text":"will severely impact breadbaskets of the world,"},{"time":965000,"text":"causing massive famines"},{"time":967000,"text":"and economic decline."},{"time":971000,"text":"Imagine a giant asteroid"},{"time":974000,"text":"on a direct collision course with Earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":978000,"text":"That is the equivalent"},{"time":980000,"text":"of what we face now."},{"time":982000,"text":"Yet, we dither,"},{"time":984000,"text":"taking no action"},{"time":986000,"text":"to divert the asteroid,"},{"time":988000,"text":"even though the longer we wait,"},{"time":990000,"text":"the more difficult and expensive it becomes."},{"time":994000,"text":"If we had started in 2005,"},{"time":996000,"text":"it would have required emission reductions of three percent per year"},{"time":999000,"text":"to restore planetary energy balance"},{"time":1002000,"text":"and stabilize climate this century."},{"time":1005000,"text":"If we start next year,"},{"time":1007000,"text":"it is six percent per year."},{"time":1009000,"text":"If we wait 10 years, it is 15 percent per year --"},{"time":1012000,"text":"extremely difficult and expensive,"},{"time":1014000,"text":"perhaps impossible."},{"time":1017000,"text":"But we aren't even starting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1019000,"text":"So now you know what I know"},{"time":1022000,"text":"that is moving me to sound this alarm."},{"time":1025000,"text":"Clearly, I haven't gotten this message across."},{"time":1028000,"text":"The science is clear."},{"time":1031000,"text":"I need your help"},{"time":1033000,"text":"to communicate the gravity and the urgency"},{"time":1035000,"text":"of this situation"},{"time":1037000,"text":"and its solutions"},{"time":1039000,"text":"more effectively."},{"time":1041000,"text":"We owe it to our children and grandchildren."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1043000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1045000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}